Here it is… fresh off the grill, your 2023 @phillyinquirer dining guide! This cover shot from the inimitable @monicaherndon says it all: Philly’s restaurant scene is smoking hot. Beginning with this giant river prawn for the goon phao at @kalaya. 

I spent two months this summer munching my way through 40+ restaurants, and really, I could have written several different renditions of this guide - our dining scene is so deep, so diverse, so dynamic. But this year’s final Top 10 reflects that energy best, with a blend of exciting new talents and longtime standard-bearers still at the top of their game, spanning the region. Congrats to them all (listed below), but also to the 15 other places I singled out for some of the best dishes in Philly right now, the 5 other important newcomers I’ve noted, and also the 5 longtime favorites that are still excellent, but now virtually impossible to score a table at (a.k.a. ‘The Impossibles’)....that doesn’t mean I won’t keep trying! 

As always, a major project like this requires real teamwork, so major thanks to my former editor @jamilarobinson , the Inquirer’s deputy food editor @margareteby , deputy features editor (& digital design wiz)  @eaweiss, @joeybear85 and also my colleagues @jrladd and @phillyinsider for *their* excellent contributions to the guide. Thanks to all the photographers and also designer @antonklusener for making it so beautiful. 

The magazine is included today for all subscribers, and also in all newsstand copies through today. Meanwhile, check the gorgeous online edition through link in my bio. Aside from cover shot, all pics in this post are mine from the field…

Congrats to this year’s Top 10, which, as always, is unranked. And Happy Eating Philadelphia!!!! 
